# TypeScript

- Use strict typing: no `any`, no non-null assertions, and no unchecked casts.
- Use named exports only.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports.
- Add explicit return types for exported functions and components.
- Prefer early returns to reduce nesting and complexity.
- Keep files under 200 lines and functions under 40 lines.
- Add a comment to each file describing what this file does
- Keep reusable logic in `components/ui` or `lib` instead of duplicating in pages.
- Prefer `@/` aliases for frontend imports when available.